00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:20,625
to ordinary things what if your morning commute

294
00:12:20,708 --> 00:12:23,916
that boring team meeting or folding laundry

295
00:12:23,916 --> 00:12:26,916
could be just as meaningful as summiting Everest

296
00:12:27,791 --> 00:12:31,083
this leads us to the most counterintuitive truth of all

297
00:12:35,916 --> 00:12:36,750
what if I told you

298
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:38,375
the most meaningful life might come from

299
00:12:38,375 --> 00:12:40,208
stopping the search for meaning entirely

300
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:42,000
stay with me here

301
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:45,166
this is where things get weird and profound

302
00:12:45,958 --> 00:12:46,833
remember those moments

303
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:48,666
when you were so absorbed in something

304
00:12:48,916 --> 00:12:51,458
maybe playing music or hiking in nature

305
00:12:51,458 --> 00:12:53,625
or deep in conversation with a friend

306
00:12:53,833 --> 00:12:55,625
that you completely forgot yourself

307
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:00,125
time disappeared your problems vanished

308
00:13:00,125 --> 00:13:02,375
and you were just there

309
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:05,833
those moments of flow of complete presence

310
00:13:06,041 --> 00:13:07,958
that's what Buddhism is pointing toward

311
00:13:08,625 --> 00:13:10,000
not some grand purpose

312
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,500
that makes your life significant in the cosmic scheme

313
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:15,333
but the simple miracle of being fully alive

314
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:16,291
in this moment

315
00:13:17,333 --> 00:13:19,500
Buddhist teacher Thich Nhat Hanh said

316
00:13:19,541 --> 00:13:21,666
the miracle is not to walk on water

317
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:24,083
the miracle is to walk on the green earth

318
00:13:24,166 --> 00:13:25,916
dwelling deeply in the present moment

319
00:13:25,916 --> 00:13:28,041
and feeling truly alive

320
00:13:28,958 --> 00:13:31,625
