00:13:36,166 --> 00:13:37,333
nothing special

324
00:13:37,541 --> 00:13:40,625
but suddenly I wasn't watching the sunset

325
00:13:41,041 --> 00:13:43,000
I was the sunset

326
00:13:43,583 --> 00:13:47,291
the boundary between me and the world just dissolved

327
00:13:48,291 --> 00:13:50,291
for those few minutes there was no Matt

328
00:13:50,291 --> 00:13:52,250
trying to figure out the point of his life

329
00:13:52,541 --> 00:13:55,125
there was just life happening

330
00:13:56,125 --> 00:13:57,458
and it was enough

331
00:13:59,875 --> 00:14:02,291
Buddhist teacher Jack Cornfield reminds us

332
00:14:02,375 --> 00:14:04,625
the trouble is you think you have time

333
00:14:04,958 --> 00:14:07,208
we're constantly postponing our lives

334
00:14:07,291 --> 00:14:09,083
waiting for meaning to arrive

335
00:14:09,166 --> 00:14:10,875
waiting to figure it all out

336
00:14:10,958 --> 00:14:12,500
but life is happening now

337
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:13,958
while we're making other plans

338
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:16,750
when we stop demanding that life have some grand

339
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:19,375
purpose something paradoxical happens

340
00:14:19,791 --> 00:14:22,541
we find ourselves naturally drawn to what matters

341
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:26,666
we stop asking what's the point and start asking

342
00:14:26,791 --> 00:14:28,125
what's needed here

343
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:31,708
how can I help what wants to come through me

344
00:14:32,791 --> 00:14:35,000
the Japanese concept of ikigai

345
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:36,666
your reason for being

346
00:14:37,041 --> 00:14:39,500
isn't something you discover once and for all

347
00:14:39,958 --> 00:14:41,916
it's something you practice daily

348
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,791
through the way you engage with your ordinary life

349
00:14:45,291 --> 00:14:47,916
this isn't giving up it's not nihilism

350
00:14:48,041 --> 00:14:50,708
it's actually the most engaged way to live

351
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:53,791
when we stop treating life like a problem to solve

352
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:57,666
or a test to pass we can finally show up for it fully

353
00:14:58,208 --> 00:14:59,333
and that brings us to

354
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:01,500
the ultimate plot twist in Buddha's teachings

355
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:09,000
so what is the meaning of life according to Buddha

356
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:13,041
ready for the plot twist there isn't one fixed meaning

357
00:15:13,208 --> 00:15:15,000
and that's actually the good news

358
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:18,000
in our video Buddha's Emptiness explained

359
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,750
we talked about how nothing has inherent fixed meaning

360
00:15:21,166 --> 00:15:23,500
and while that might sound depressing at first

361
00:15:23,583 --> 00:15:25,625
it's actually incredibly liberating

362
00:15:26,208 --> 00:15:28,458
life doesn't come with meaning pre installed

363
00:15:28,458 --> 00:15:30,458
we create meaning through how we live

364
00:15:30,541 --> 00:15:32,791
through our choices our connections

365
00:15:32,791 --> 00:15:33,750
our presence

366
00:15:34,666 --> 00:15:37,208
here's the radical truth Buddha was pointing to

367
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:39,541
life isn't meaningful because of what we achieve

368
00:15:39,541 --> 00:15:40,666
or accumulate

369
00:15:40,875 --> 00:15:43,750
it's meaningful because we're here to experience it

370
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:45,958
to taste it to feel it

371
00:15:45,958 --> 00:15:47,500
to connect through it

372
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:51,041
the meaning isn't in reaching Nirvana someday

373
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:54,000
the meaning is in how you walk the path today

374
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:56,333
I remember asking my teacher

375
00:15:56,333 --> 00:15:57,208
but what's the point

376
00:15:57,208 --> 00:15:59,000
if we're all just going to die anyway

377
00:15:59,791 --> 00:16:01,666
she laughed and said Matt

378
00:16:01,666 --> 00:16:03,958
do you only eat pizza if it lasts forever

379
00:16:04,458 --> 00:16:06,000
do you refuse to watch Netflix

380
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,041
because the series will eventually end

381
00:16:08,458 --> 00:16:09,916
do you avoid falling in love

382
00:16:09,916 --> 00:16:11,833
because all relationships change

383
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:14,291
your question is like deleting Spotify

384
00:16:14,291 --> 00:16:15,583
because songs have endings

385
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:19,041
the point is the experience itself

386
00:16:19,208 --> 00:16:21,166
the taste the sound

387
00:16:21,250 --> 00:16:22,250
the feeling

388
00:16:22,791 --> 00:16:25,666
the point is being fully here for whatever is happening

389
00:16:25,666 --> 00:16:27,458
even if it's just washing those dishes

390
00:16:27,458 --> 00:16:28,750
we talked about earlier

391
00:16:29,791 --> 00:16:31,916
Buddhism isn't about escaping life

392
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:35,083
it's about showing up for it completely pain

393
00:16:35,291 --> 00:16:37,000
joy boredom

394
00:16:37,125 --> 00:16:39,208
excitement all of it

395
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:40,875
it's about bringing your full

396
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:43,166
attention to whatever is happening right now

397
00:16:44,375 --> 00:16:47,416
the 4 Noble truths aren't a pessimistic declaration

398
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:48,666
that life is suffering

399
00:16:49,041 --> 00:16:50,666
they're a realistic acknowledgement

400
00:16:50,666 --> 00:16:52,541
that life contains suffering

401
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:55,666
and a practical path to transforming our relationship

402
00:16:55,666 --> 00:16:56,791
with that suffering

403
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:58,708
the meaning of life

404
00:16:58,708 --> 00:17:00,958
isn't something to figure out intellectually

405
00:17:01,208 --> 00:17:03,625
it's something to embody through how we live

406
00:17:03,875 --> 00:17:06,333
so if you're still wondering what the point of life is

407
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:08,291
maybe try asking a different question

408
00:17:08,666 --> 00:17:11,000
instead of what's the point

409
00:17:11,375 --> 00:17:14,833
ask what's possible right now

410
00:17:15,875 --> 00:17:18,000
how can I be fully here for this one

411
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:20,708
precious moment that will never come again

412
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:24,250
because that's what Buddha was really pointing to

413
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:26,000
not some distant enlightenment

414
00:17:26,083 --> 00:17:27,791
but the immediate freedom available

415
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:30,500
when we stop chasing stop resisting

416
00:17:30,708 --> 00:17:33,333
and simply show up for our lives as they are

417
00:17:33,916 --> 00:17:35,333
that's the ultimate meaning

418
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:36,875
not something we find

419
00:17:36,875 --> 00:17:39,750
but something we create moment by moment

420
00:17:40,041 --> 00:17:41,583
through the quality of our attention

421
00:17:41,583 --> 00:17:43,333
and the openness of our hearts

422
00:17:43,875 --> 00:17:47,000
for me that means spending less time doomscrolling

423
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,000
and more time actually

424
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,250
looking into the eyes of people I'm talking to

425
00:17:50,791 --> 00:17:52,291
it means tasting my food

426
00:17:52,291 --> 00:17:54,458
instead of inhaling it while watching YouTube

427
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,750
it means feeling the sun on my skin

428
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:58,541
and remembering that someday

429
00:17:58,541 --> 00:17:59,791
this ordinary Tuesday

430
00:17:59,791 --> 00:18:01,916
might be the day I look back on and think

431
00:18:02,083 --> 00:18:04,625
that was life that was it

432
00:18:05,666 --> 00:18:07,208
picture yourself years from now

433
00:18:07,208 --> 00:18:08,666
looking back at this moment

434
00:18:08,833 --> 00:18:10,791
not at your achievements or possessions

435
00:18:11,041 --> 00:18:13,916
but at how fully you lived each ordinary day

436
00:18:14,083 --> 00:18:14,625
the mornings

437
00:18:14,625 --> 00:18:17,250
you noticed the steam rising from your coffee cup

438
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,958
the times you really listened to a friend

